Message:
Update official Vulkan branch (#1244)

* Removed unwanted matrix mul calls from the daydream renderer

* Enable native debugging for the fw and the backends

GearVRf-DCO-1.0-Signed-off-by: Mihail Marinov <m.marinov@samsung.com>

* Back key handling improvements

GearVRf-DCO-1.0-Signed-off-by: Mihail Marinov <m.marinov@samsung.com>

* Add default gvr.xml; add overloads for setMain and setScript
that omit the configuration file

GearVRf-DCO-1.0-Signed-off-by: Mihail Marinov <m.marinov@samsung.com>

* Force NDK_DEBUG to 1 for all builds in case the framework and the demos
are configured to be built together.

Add "buildGvrfAndDemos=true" to your gradle.properties to enable building
the framework, backends and the demos together. And also to be able to
debug.

Looks like gradle packages the release .so in the apk no matter what..
And also builds the release target even though nobody asks for it.

* Introduce LOD component(s)

GearVRf-DCO-1.0-Signed-off-by: Mihail Marinov <m.marinov@samsung.com>

* Improvements and cleanup

GearVRf-DCO-1.0-Signed-off-by: Mihail Marinov <m.marinov@samsung.com>

* Clean up of the head tracking processing for Oculus

There were redundant ApplyHeadModel calls and generally
streamlined the code.

I find a subtle improvement with this change - on Note5
which has no frame dropping issue like S7.

Added APIs to GVRAssetLoader which take a GVRResourceVolume instead of a String to describe the asset to load. This allows callers to subclass GVRResourceVolume to provide custom loading behavior. Modified GVRResourceVolume to keep the filename it was intially created with.

* Trying to troubleshoot the automated build: rename packageForPlugins to packageFrameworkForPlugins

* Fix for issue #967, "Texture goes missing ..."

Custom shaders can and do get reused. If any of the materials of the scene
objects using the same shader introduces a new texture key, the custom
shader instance will start checking for the key for all scene objects it
renders. If there is no texture for this key, the texture presence check
at the start of CustomShader::render will fail and not render the scene
object.

I am undecided whether in this case something needs to be done about sharing
shaders but am sure that the check by CustomShader:render is both
undesirable and obsolete. Hence I removed it.

Also disabled a bunch of GL error checking by default.

* Fix import of shininess in X3D

The X3D shininess value is between 0 and 1. The X3D spec indicates this should be scaled by 128 to match OpenGL shininess. X3D shininess does NOT correspond to the roughness parameter in physically based shading models.

	for OpenGL ES, we will detect this version and rewrite the shader, removing layout directives. Replace version with "300 es"

Update local locking logic (#1842)

This patch is made to address some issues with local locking, that is
the locking that deals with the .pid files typically in each machines
/tmp/luigi folder.

There's one bugfix (can massively improve startup performence):

  * Don't keep old entries in the .pid files

There's one change in logic:

  * When running with --take-lock, only allow for one "additional" task
    being run, the previous behavior was that --take-lock tasks always
    could keep running. With this new behavior, it could perhaps be
    possible to always cron your lines with --take-lock.

Lastly, there was much refactoring of the code. Although longer, I find
the readability to have drastcially improved.

Allow wiring of <hz-dynamic-table> into <transfer-table>

The framework change consists of 2 parts:

* Provide filterAvailable filter to be used inside 'items' value of
  <hz-dynamic-table> instead of 'ng-if' directve which was used before
  in manually written table layout (no longer possible with dynamic
  tables). This filter solves the task of hiding the available values
  once they become allocated.
* Provide 'allocateItemAction' and 'deallocateItemAction' actions on
  transfer-table controller which are compatible with 'itemActions'
  attribute of <hz-dynamic-table>.

Keypairs tab in Angular Launch Instance wizard is rewritten to use the
new approach.

Also a nasty bug within <hz-dynamic-table> was fixed: `scope.items`
value was set in hz-dynamic-table's post-linking function before,
which lead to `undefined` value arriving into st-table directive,
because st-table was linked before hz-dynamic-table as its child
(that's how postLink function works). Directive st-table under some
circustances was wrapping `undefined` into `[]`, causing various
issues with table row equal to `undefined`. The solution to that
problem was to extract setting `scope.items = []` to a pre-linking
function, so by the time st-table is linked, there is already an empty
array under scope's 'items' property.
